{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 XML documents can hold more than just text. By using a format called Base64 encoding, the text in the XML can hold images, RTF, or any other bitmap file.\par
\par
In this example, you can add RTF notes to the Contacts list. Use the View Raw XML button to see how the Base64 encoding is stored in the XML.\par
\par
You will notice in the code that there was little special handling of the Base64 field. Since it is an RTF Blob, it had to be displayed in an RTF Control, but beyond that, all the translation was done automatically by Magic.\par
}

